#\#CIF_2.0
# Tests: quoted sentinel encoding. Single-quoted '.' and '?' are QUOTED strings,
# not PLACEHOLDERs. They must be stored as '"."' and '"?"' in structured columns
# so they can be distinguished from the unquoted PLACEHOLDER forms on round-trip.
# ValueType must survive ingestion unchanged.
#
# Note that the values of _diffrn_source.make as a quote-string of a quoted question mark
# is lost
#
# Dictionary: cif_core

data_test_quoted_sentinel
_cell.length_a    5.000
_cell.length_b    5.000
_cell.length_c    5.000
_cell.angle_alpha 90
_cell.angle_beta  90
_cell.angle_gamma 90

_diffrn_source.beamline     "."
_diffrn_source.description  "?"
_diffrn_source.details  """?"""
_diffrn_source.device   '''?'''
_diffrn_source.facility
;?
;
_diffrn_source.make '"?"'















